# ResearchGPT Configuration Guide

# ==================================================================
# CRITICAL: Backend Server Configuration
# ==================================================================
# The backend server (server.js) handles CORS and proxies API requests
# It runs on port 3001 by default
#
# To start in development:
#   npm install
#   npm run dev
#
# This runs both the Vite dev server (port 5173) and backend (port 3001)
# ===================================================================

# ===================================================================
# API Configuration
# ===================================================================

# CORE API - Optional but Recommended for more papers
# Free API key from: https://core.ac.uk/api
# Process:
#   1. Visit https://core.ac.uk/api
#   2. Click "Get API Key" button
#   3. Sign up with your email
#   4. Verify your email
#   5. Copy your API key and paste below
#
# Free tier: 200 requests/hour
# If not provided, app will still fetch from arXiv + Semantic Scholar
VITE_CORE_API_KEY=

# Optional Debug Mode
# Set to true to see detailed logs about paper fetching
VITE_DEBUG=false

# ===================================================================
# Backend Server Settings (optional - usually auto-configured)
# ===================================================================
PORT=3001
NODE_ENV=development

# ===================================================================
# Notes:
# ===================================================================
# - arXiv API: Always free, 100% of papers have PDFs
# - Semantic Scholar: Free with rate limits, ~40-60% have open access PDFs
# - CORE API: Free with API key, excellent for AI/ML papers
#
# If papers aren't fetching:
#   1. Check that 'npm run dev' is running both server and Vite
#   2. Check browser console (F12) for errors
#   3. Ensure VITE_CORE_API_KEY is correct if using CORE
#   4. Try simpler search terms: "machine learning", "deep learning"
